Checks for different PCIe Protocol error generation (upstram/downstream) and check the clear mechanism of AFU for these detected protocol errors. 1. Apply the error. 2. Wait 5us 1us 3. Set the port reset bit true and then false again (within 1us) (You will not be able to perform a read-modify-write because Fs will be retuened on resds. Write a 0x5 to set and a 0x4 to clear). 4. Wait 124us 135us (or 7.5us 28us if MMIO_TIMEOUT_CYCLES is 512.) 5. Read bit 31 of the AFU_INTF_ERROR, BlockingTraffic. If it is set it means that we did not wait long enough in step 4. 6. Read the AFU_INTF_ERROR register, Be sure only the expected error(s) are set. 7. Read the AFU_INTF_FIRST_ERROR CSR. Be sure only one error bit is set and it is the expected one. 8. Clear the errors in the AFU_INTF_ERROR CSR by writing one to the bits that are set. 9. Read the AFU_INTF_FIRST_ERROR CSR. Be sure all bits are cleared
